
[1]dissection

   DISSECTION, n. [L.]

   1. The act of cutting in pieces an animal or vegetable, for the purpose
   of examining the structure and uses of its parts; anatomy.

   Dissection was held sacrilege till the time of Francis I.

   2.The act of separating into constituent parts, for the purpose of
   critical examination.
